    "description": "I came across a bug in AMRSmoothedCoveringGrid that would probably only come up for codes like Orion that use cgs units. Basically, I would occasionally get round-off errors in the code that computed indices for the covering grid. This would result in array size errors like the one Elizabeth Tasker posted to the list last week, but the root cause seems to be different here. The fix was to switch \"self.right_edge - self.left_edge\" with it's algebriac equivalent \"self.ActiveDimensions*self.dds. These should always be the same were not due to floating point weirdness. Smoothed covering grids work for me after this change. ",
